<p>This poem, by Lewis Carroll, can be read line by line in the conventional way, but the same text results when it&#8217;s scanned &#8220;downward&#8221; in columns, reading the first word of each of the six lines, then the second, and so on:</p>
<pre>
I           often     wondered    when     I         cursed

Often       feared    where       I        would     be --

Wondered    where     she'd       yield    her       love,

When        I         yield,      so       will      she.

I           would     her         will     be        pitied!

Cursed      be        love!       She      pitied    me ...
</pre>
